commit.title: Clarifying that the "print" functions in Names are mainly for debugging.
commit.message:
Clarifying that the "print" functions in Names are mainly for debugging.

The "print" and "to_string" functions in Names were printing full
names (not taking into account visibility). They were also printing
"#" for sections, which is not part of the user-level syntax of names.

We requalify them as "debug" printers. This allows to catch quite a
number of misuses of these functions in code supposed to be read by the
user.

Use of these printers in reporting anomalies are expected and were
kept.

Still not perfect (see a few FIXME).
